The paper deals with resource allocation games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for learning in these games, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.AI) and learning theory (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves graph-based optimization, which is a topic in computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the observability model, which is related to control theory (cs.SY).
